1. Not all immigrants live off US taxpayers. Many contribute more in taxes than they receive in benefits.2. The US has a long history of welcoming immigrants and has benefited greatly from their contributions to society.3. It's important to remember that everyone deserves basic human rights and dignity, regardless of their nationality or economic situation.4. Sending people back to countries where they may face danger or poverty is not a solution. Instead, we should focus on addressing the root causes of migration and work towards creating a more just and equitable world.5. "Make America Great Again" does not mean turning our backs on the rest of the world. It means making America a beacon of hope, opportunity, and compassion for all people.
